The paper deals with compressive sensing (CS) and focuses on the phase-only compressive sensing (PO-CS) scenario. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of linear compressive sensing models and matrix properties, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results, which suggest the use of numerical algorithms, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category as well.
